                                branch agreement on consolidating communications facilities abroad;
                                State/Attorney General agreement concerning the FBI’s Legal attache program);

—address all agencies of the Executive Branch not only those with
                                overseas missions, since you are requiring control of overseas
                                travel by all U.S. Government employees;

—clarify the fact that new regulations to control travel abroad
                                will be in addition to, not instead of, current requirements for
                                clearing travel plans with the Department of State;
